ISLAMABAD, Mar 15 (APP): Minister of State for Information and Broadcasting Farrukh Habib on Tuesday said Prime Minister Imran Khan had became pride of the whole Islamic world as the United Nations adopted a resolution, moved by Pakistan on behalf of the OIC, declaring March 15 as an International Day to Combat Islamophobia.
He, in a tweet, said the prime minister presented the case of entire Muslim Ummah against Islamophobia at the UN General Assembly in 2019.
